const p1 = [
  mc('responsible-ai','medium','A loan-ranking model approves equally qualified applicants at different rates across demographic groups. What should the team investigate first?','Whether training data and evaluation results reveal unfair performance differences',['Whether response latency is identical in every region','Whether the model uses the maximum token limit','Whether generated explanations use Markdown'],'Fairness requires measuring whether comparable people receive comparable quality and outcomes. Regional latency and formatting do not diagnose unequal model performance.'),
  mc('responsible-ai','easy','A hospital uses an AI recommendation only after a clinician reviews the evidence and can reject it. Which principle does this control support most directly?','Accountability',['Inclusiveness','Image classification','Speech synthesis'],'Accountability keeps people and organizations responsible for consequential decisions. A reviewer with authority provides oversight; the other choices describe accessibility or technical workloads.'),
  dd('responsible-ai','medium','{{blank}} is supported by giving users clear notice that an answer was generated by AI.','transparency',['elasticity','clustering','speech recognition'],'Transparency helps people understand when AI is involved and what its limitations are. Elasticity is an infrastructure property, while clustering and speech recognition are AI techniques.'),
  sg('responsible-ai','hard','For each proposed control, decide whether it directly supports responsible deployment.','yes-no',[["Test safety behavior with representative high-risk prompts before release",true],["Assume a high benchmark score removes the need for production monitoring",false],["Provide no route for users to challenge consequential outcomes",false]],'Pre-release evaluation, ongoing monitoring, and meaningful recourse are lifecycle controls. A benchmark is evidence, not a guarantee, and removing recourse weakens responsible deployment.'),
  ms('responsible-ai','hard','Which TWO actions most directly improve privacy and security for an app that sends customer records to a model?',['Remove unnecessary personal fields before requests are sent','Restrict access to prompts, outputs, and logs'],['Increase temperature for sensitive requests','Publish raw prompts for unrestricted troubleshooting'],'Data minimization reduces exposed information, while access controls protect retained data. Sampling temperature does not secure data, and publishing raw prompts expands exposure.'),
  ms('responsible-ai','medium','Which TWO design choices make an AI service more inclusive?',['Test the experience with people who have varied abilities','Provide interaction alternatives such as text and speech'],['Use one language and input method for consistency','Measure only the average response time'],'Inclusive design considers a range of abilities and contexts and offers usable alternatives. A single interaction path and an average latency metric do not establish accessibility.'),

  mc('model-components','medium','A support assistant must answer from frequently updated internal manuals and cite the relevant passages. Which approach should be evaluated first?','Ground the model with retrieval from the approved manuals',['Fine-tune the model every time a manual changes','Raise temperature so the model recalls more facts','Use image generation to create citations'],'Retrieval supplies current approved material at request time and can preserve source links. Fine-tuning is not an efficient document-update mechanism, and temperature or image generation cannot add verified knowledge.'),
  mc('model-components','easy','What does a token represent when a generative model processes a prompt?','A unit of text processed by the model',['A user identity stored in Microsoft Entra ID','A confidence score for an extracted field','A deployed virtual machine instance'],'Tokens are the text units a model consumes and produces when calculating context and output limits. They are unrelated to identity tokens, extraction confidence, or compute instances.'),
  mc('model-components','hard','Two models meet an accuracy target, but one costs less and responds faster under the expected load. What is the best deployment choice?','Use the lower-cost, lower-latency model after representative evaluation',['Always deploy the model with the largest parameter count','Select whichever model appears first in the catalog','Increase the slower model’s maximum output tokens'],'Model choice should balance measured quality, latency, throughput, and cost for the workload. Size, catalog order, and larger outputs do not by themselves improve suitability.'),
  dd('model-components','easy','To limit how long a generated response can become, configure the {{blank}} parameter.','maximum output tokens',['temperature','embedding dimensions','content filter category'],'Maximum output tokens sets an upper bound on generated length. Temperature affects sampling variation, while embedding dimensions and content-filter categories serve different purposes.'),
  sg('model-components','medium','Evaluate each statement about generative-model configuration.','true-false',[["Lower temperature generally makes sampling more consistent",true],["Grounding permanently changes the model weights",false],["A model should be evaluated on representative inputs before deployment",true]],'Temperature influences output variation, and evaluation measures suitability on the intended workload. Grounding adds context at request time rather than modifying model weights.'),
  ms('model-components','hard','Which TWO requirements most strongly indicate that a multimodal model is needed?',['The request includes a photograph that must be interpreted','The response must relate visual evidence to written instructions'],['The response must contain fewer than 100 tokens','The client uses environment variables for configuration'],'Multimodal capability is required when a model must reason over visual and textual inputs together. Output length and application configuration do not determine input modality.'),

  mc('ai-workloads','easy','A retailer predicts the numeric value of next month’s sales from historical data. Which machine-learning task is this?','Regression',['Classification','Clustering','Object detection'],'Regression predicts a continuous numeric value such as sales. Classification predicts categories, clustering discovers groups, and object detection locates items in images.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','easy','A system assigns incoming messages to billing, technical support, or sales. Which task is being performed?','Multiclass classification',['Regression','Image segmentation','Speech synthesis'],'Multiclass classification selects one category from several possible labels. The required output is neither numeric, pixel-level, nor synthesized audio.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','medium','A manufacturer has no failure labels and wants to discover unusual sensor readings. Which technique fits the requirement?','Anomaly detection',['Supervised classification','Text summarization','Image generation'],'Anomaly detection finds observations that depart from learned normal patterns and does not require labeled failure classes. The other techniques solve different output problems.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','medium','A photo-processing system must return the location of every vehicle as rectangular coordinates. Which vision capability is required?','Object detection',['Image classification','Optical character recognition','Sentiment analysis'],'Object detection identifies instances and returns their locations, commonly as bounding boxes. Classification labels a whole image, OCR reads text, and sentiment analyzes language.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','medium','A call center needs written transcripts of customer conversations. Which AI capability supplies the required first output?','Speech recognition',['Speech synthesis','Key phrase extraction','Image captioning'],'Speech recognition converts spoken audio into text that downstream analytics can process. Synthesis performs the reverse, while key phrases and captions operate on other inputs.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','hard','An app must extract merchant, tax, and total fields from varied receipt images. Which workload best describes the requirement?','Structured information extraction',['Free-form image generation','Document sentiment analysis','Unsupervised clustering'],'The desired output is a defined set of fields grounded in source images, which is structured extraction. The task does not create an image, infer opinion, or discover unlabeled groups.'),
  dd('ai-workloads','easy','{{blank}} finds organization names and locations in a news article.','named entity recognition',['speech synthesis','object detection','regression'],'Named entity recognition finds and categorizes mentions such as organizations and places in text. The alternatives operate on audio, images, or numeric prediction.'),
  sg('ai-workloads','medium','For each scenario, decide whether the named workload is appropriate.','yes-no',[["Use summarization to produce a short account of a long report",true],["Use sentiment analysis to find every person named in an email",false],["Use supervised classification to discover groups when no labels exist",false]],'Summarization condenses content. Named entity recognition—not sentiment—finds people in text, and clustering—not supervised classification—discovers groups when labels are absent.'),
  ms('ai-workloads','hard','Which TWO outputs are characteristic of an object-detection solution?',['A class label for each detected object','Coordinates locating each detected object'],['A sentiment score for the whole image','A spoken version of the image file name'],'Object detection identifies what each object is and where it appears. Sentiment and speech output are unrelated to locating visual objects.'),
  ms('ai-workloads','medium','Which TWO capabilities are required for a kiosk that accepts spoken questions and reads answers aloud?',['Speech recognition for the input','Speech synthesis for the output'],['OCR for the input','Image segmentation for the output'],'A voice interaction needs speech-to-text processing for spoken input and text-to-speech processing for audible output. OCR and segmentation process visual data.'),

  mc('foundry-generative','medium','A team wants to configure instructions, a model, and file search in the Foundry portal without maintaining custom orchestration code. What should it create?','A prompt agent',['A hosted agent with custom packages','A Content Understanding analyzer','An Azure virtual network gateway'],'A prompt agent is configured declaratively with instructions, a model, and tools. Hosted agents are for custom orchestration, while analyzers and gateways solve different problems.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','hard','A Python agent uses a custom orchestration framework and extra packages. The team wants Foundry-managed hosting and observability. Which agent type fits?','A hosted agent',['A prompt agent with no custom runtime','A speech transcription deployment','A document storage account'],'Hosted agents run custom code and dependencies in a managed Agent Service environment. Prompt agents do not provide an arbitrary custom runtime, and the other services are not agent hosts.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','easy','Which prompt role should contain enduring instructions about an assistant’s behavior and boundaries?','The system prompt',['The latest user message','A retrieved document chunk','The model deployment name'],'System instructions establish persistent behavior and constraints for the conversation. User content and retrieved data should not replace higher-priority instructions, and deployment names are configuration.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','medium','An agent needs to answer from uploaded product manuals. Which built-in tool is the most direct fit?','File search',['Code interpreter','Speech synthesis','Image generation'],'File search retrieves relevant passages from uploaded knowledge sources for grounded answers. The other tools execute code or create audio or images rather than search documents.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','medium','An agent must calculate totals and produce a chart from an uploaded CSV file. Which tool should be added?','Code interpreter',['File search only','Text to speech','Entity recognition'],'Code interpreter can execute code over uploaded data for calculations and charts. Retrieval and language or speech analysis alone do not perform the requested computation.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','hard','Before an agent executes a money-transfer function, what is the most important application control?','Validate the arguments and require authorization or confirmation',['Raise temperature to explore alternative transfers','Hide the tool call from audit logs','Grant the model unrestricted administrator access'],'High-impact tools need validated inputs, scoped authorization, and often explicit confirmation. Greater randomness, reduced auditability, or excessive privilege increases rather than controls risk.'),
  dd('foundry-generative','easy','Use {{blank}} to authenticate a local Foundry SDK client without embedding a key in source code.','DefaultAzureCredential',['a public connection string','an anonymous HTTP request','a system prompt secret'],'DefaultAzureCredential can obtain a Microsoft Entra token from supported development or managed environments. Public, anonymous, or prompt-embedded secrets are not safe authentication patterns.'),
  dd('foundry-generative','medium','To compare model responses interactively before writing client code, begin in the Foundry {{blank}}.','playground',['billing export','DNS zone','resource lock'],'A Foundry playground supports interactive prompt and model testing before application integration. Billing, DNS, and resource locks do not provide model inference experiments.'),
  sg('foundry-generative','hard','Evaluate each statement about building a Foundry application.','true-false',[["Representative evaluations should be run before replacing a production model",true],["Retrieved text should be allowed to override system instructions",false],["Tracing can help diagnose model and tool steps",true]],'Evaluation and tracing support controlled releases and diagnosis. Retrieved content is untrusted data and must not be permitted to replace higher-priority application instructions.'),
  ms('foundry-generative','medium','Which TWO components are needed by a lightweight client that calls a deployed model securely?',['The correct project or model endpoint','A supported credential with appropriate access'],['A password embedded in browser JavaScript','An image analyzer for every text request'],'A client needs the correct endpoint and an authorized credential. Embedding secrets in a browser is unsafe, and a visual analyzer is unnecessary for text-only requests.'),

  mc('foundry-text-speech','easy','Which text-analysis capability returns whether customer feedback is positive, neutral, or negative?','Sentiment analysis',['Entity recognition','Speech translation','Object detection'],'Sentiment analysis estimates expressed opinion or polarity in text. Entity recognition finds named things, translation works with languages, and detection locates visual objects.'),
  mc('foundry-text-speech','medium','A company wants the most important nouns and phrases from thousands of support messages. Which capability should it use?','Key phrase extraction',['Speech synthesis','Image classification','Regression'],'Key phrase extraction identifies salient words and phrases in text. The alternatives create audio, label images, or predict numeric values.'),
  mc('foundry-text-speech','hard','A meeting recording must be transcribed asynchronously after it ends. Which Speech capability is most appropriate?','Batch transcription',['Real-time speech synthesis','Image understanding','Text sentiment analysis'],'Batch transcription is designed for processing stored audio asynchronously. Synthesis creates audio, while image and sentiment workloads do not transcribe speech.'),
  dd('foundry-text-speech','easy','Converting generated text into audible narration uses speech {{blank}}.','synthesis',['recognition','clustering','segmentation'],'Speech synthesis converts text into spoken audio. Recognition converts audio to text, while clustering and segmentation solve unrelated analytical tasks.'),
  sg('foundry-text-speech','medium','Evaluate each statement about language and speech capabilities.','yes-no',[["Entity recognition can identify people and organizations in text",true],["Speech synthesis converts an audio recording into a transcript",false],["Language detection translates text into every supported language",false]],'Entity recognition finds named things. Speech recognition—not synthesis—produces a transcript, and language detection identifies a language without performing translation.'),
  ms('foundry-text-speech','hard','Which TWO features can improve a speech-recognition solution for specialist vocabulary and multi-speaker meetings?',['A phrase list or custom speech model for domain terms','Speaker diarization to distinguish speakers'],['A higher image resolution','An Azure Policy initiative for punctuation'],'Vocabulary adaptation can improve recognition of domain terms, and diarization separates speakers. Image resolution and governance initiatives do not change transcription behavior.'),

  mc('foundry-vision','easy','A quality-control app must decide whether an entire image shows a cracked component. Which capability is sufficient?','Image classification',['Object detection with bounding boxes','Speech recognition','Key phrase extraction'],'Image classification assigns a label to the whole image, which fits a single cracked-or-not result. Bounding boxes are needed only when locations or multiple instances matter.'),
  mc('foundry-vision','medium','A user submits a photograph and asks a model to explain the visible safety hazard. What model capability is required?','Visual input understanding in a multimodal model',['Text-only embeddings','Speech synthesis','Time-series forecasting'],'The model must interpret visual evidence together with a text instruction, requiring multimodal visual understanding. Text embeddings, audio generation, and forecasting do not inspect images.'),
  mc('foundry-vision','medium','A design tool must create a new product illustration from a written description. Which workload should it use?','Image generation',['Optical character recognition','Object detection','Sentiment analysis'],'Image generation creates new visual content from a prompt. OCR reads existing text, detection locates existing objects, and sentiment evaluates language.'),
  dd('foundry-vision','easy','{{blank}} returns the text printed on a photographed shipping label.','optical character recognition',['speech translation','image generation','regression'],'Optical character recognition extracts visible text from an image. Translation, generation, and regression do not perform visual text recognition.'),
  sg('foundry-vision','hard','Evaluate each statement about computer-vision outputs.','true-false',[["Object detection can return a bounding box for each detected item",true],["Image classification must return the coordinates of every object",false],["A multimodal model can combine an image with a written prompt",true]],'Detection includes object locations and multimodal models can use visual and textual inputs. Classification normally labels an image and does not require per-object coordinates.'),

  mc('foundry-extraction','easy','Which prebuilt Content Understanding analyzer is the most direct starting point for common invoice fields?','A prebuilt invoice analyzer',['A speech synthesis voice','A prompt agent with web search','An image-generation deployment'],'A prebuilt invoice analyzer is designed to extract established invoice structure. Speech, web search, and image generation do not provide grounded invoice field extraction.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','medium','A custom extraction solution must return policy number, claimant, and loss date. What should the analyzer define?','A schema containing those fields and clear descriptions',['A higher sampling temperature','A list of speech voices','An unrestricted tool permission'],'A field schema tells Content Understanding which structured values to extract, and descriptive definitions improve accuracy. Sampling, voices, and tool permissions do not define output structure.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','medium','Why should an app retain source locations returned with extracted fields?','They let reviewers trace values back to supporting content',['They increase the model context window','They replace access control requirements','They automatically translate every document'],'Source locations provide grounding and review evidence for extracted values. They do not change context limits, security responsibilities, or language automatically.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','hard','A company needs searchable descriptions for a large image archive before indexing it. Which Content Understanding capability is relevant?','An image analyzer that produces descriptive content',['An audio analyzer configured for diarization','A text-to-speech deployment','A classification model with no image input'],'An image analyzer can interpret visual content and return descriptions suitable for downstream indexing. Audio, speech output, or a model without visual input cannot describe the images.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','hard','An analyzer returns a low-confidence total from a damaged receipt. What should the workflow do?','Route the field for validation according to the business threshold',['Treat every returned value as certain','Delete the source receipt immediately','Raise temperature until the value changes'],'Confidence should inform validation and escalation rules, especially for consequential or poor-quality inputs. It is not a guarantee, and repeatedly changing sampling does not verify the source.'),
  dd('foundry-extraction','easy','Content Understanding uses an analyzer {{blank}} to define the structured fields an application needs.','schema',['voice','subnet','temperature'],'An analyzer schema defines field names, types, and descriptions for structured extraction. Voices, subnets, and temperature are unrelated to the requested output contract.'),
  sg('foundry-extraction','medium','Evaluate each statement about multimodal extraction.','yes-no',[["Content Understanding can process document, image, audio, and video inputs",true],["A required schema guarantees that the source contains every field",false],["Grounding information makes review of extracted values unnecessary",false]],'Content Understanding supports several content modalities and can return grounding evidence for review. Neither a schema nor grounding guarantees that every value is present or correct.'),
];

const p2 = [
  mc('responsible-ai','easy','A public benefits assistant excludes keyboard-only users from completing an application. Which responsible-AI principle is most directly affected?','Inclusiveness',['Model grounding','Elasticity','Image generation'],'Inclusiveness requires experiences that work for people with varied abilities and interaction needs. Grounding, elasticity, and image creation do not address the accessibility barrier.'),
  mc('responsible-ai','medium','A model performs well during testing but drifts after customer behavior changes. Which practice best supports reliability and safety?','Monitor production quality and define thresholds for intervention',['Stop collecting all operational signals','Assume the original test score remains valid','Increase output length for every request'],'Reliability is a lifecycle concern, so teams monitor real behavior and respond when quality changes. A historic score cannot guarantee future performance, and output length is unrelated.'),
  dd('responsible-ai','easy','{{blank}} is supported by documenting who owns an AI system and approves high-impact changes.','accountability',['clustering','speech recognition','scalability'],'Accountability assigns responsibility and governance for system decisions and changes. The alternative terms describe technical workloads or infrastructure behavior.'),
  sg('responsible-ai','hard','Decide whether each action supports transparent use of AI.','true-false',[["Tell users when they are interacting with an automated system",true],["Hide known limitations because users might lose confidence",false],["Explain the main factors used for a consequential recommendation",true]],'Transparency gives people useful notice and understandable information about operation and limitations. Concealing known limitations prevents informed use rather than improving it.'),
  ms('responsible-ai','medium','Which TWO evaluation choices best support fairness?',['Compare error rates across relevant user groups','Use representative data that includes affected populations'],['Report only one overall average','Exclude difficult cases from every test set'],'Group-level metrics and representative data can expose unequal performance hidden by averages. Removing difficult cases and reporting only aggregates can conceal harms.'),
  ms('responsible-ai','hard','Which TWO controls are most appropriate for a high-impact automated decision?',['Provide meaningful human review with authority to change the outcome','Give affected people a clear appeal or correction path'],['Treat the model score as automatically final','Remove records of how the decision was reached'],'Human oversight and recourse keep consequential decisions accountable and correctable. Automatic finality and missing records reduce the ability to identify or remedy errors.'),

  mc('model-components','easy','What is the primary purpose of an embedding model?','Represent content as numeric vectors for similarity tasks',['Generate a spoken response','Assign Azure RBAC roles','Create availability zones'],'Embeddings encode semantic characteristics as vectors that can support search and comparison. They do not synthesize speech, manage authorization, or create infrastructure.'),
  mc('model-components','medium','A model invents facts when it lacks current product information. Which change most directly addresses the missing knowledge?','Retrieve approved current content and include it as grounding context',['Increase temperature','Use a longer user name','Switch the response to audio'],'Grounding supplies relevant current evidence at inference time. Sampling variation, identity text, and output modality do not add trustworthy product knowledge.'),
  mc('model-components','hard','A team is comparing two model deployments for a mobile assistant. Which test set is most useful?','Representative mobile requests including expected edge cases',['Only the shortest successful demo prompt','Unrelated benchmark questions from another domain','One prompt selected by the model vendor'],'Evaluation should reflect real requests, constraints, and failure cases for the intended application. Narrow demos or unrelated benchmarks do not establish production suitability.'),
  dd('model-components','medium','Increasing {{blank}} generally allows more variation in generated wording.','temperature',['grounding citations','RBAC scope','embedding storage'],'Temperature influences the randomness of token sampling and therefore output variation. Citations, authorization scope, and storage do not serve as sampling controls.'),
  sg('model-components','medium','Evaluate each statement about model selection.','yes-no',[["Latency and cost can matter even when two models have similar quality",true],["The largest model is always the correct production choice",false],["Regional availability never constrains a deployment decision",false]],'A deployment choice balances measured quality with latency, cost, and regional availability. Neither model size nor an assumption of universal availability determines the best fit.'),
  ms('model-components','hard','Which TWO steps help evaluate a grounded assistant?',['Measure whether answers are supported by retrieved sources','Test retrieval with representative user wording'],['Judge only the fluency of one answer','Disable retrieval during the evaluation'],'Grounded systems require both relevant retrieval and source-supported generation. Fluency alone can hide unsupported claims, and disabling retrieval removes the behavior under test.'),

  mc('ai-workloads','easy','A service predicts whether a transaction is fraudulent or legitimate. Which task is this?','Binary classification',['Regression','Clustering','Summarization'],'Binary classification chooses between two labels such as fraud and legitimate. Regression returns a number, clustering discovers groups, and summarization condenses text.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','medium','A retailer groups customers by similar behavior without predefined segment labels. Which technique should it use?','Clustering',['Supervised classification','Speech synthesis','OCR'],'Clustering discovers natural groups in unlabeled data. Classification requires known labels, while speech synthesis and OCR process different modalities.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','easy','Which capability identifies the main topics in a document as short phrases?','Key phrase extraction',['Object detection','Speech recognition','Regression'],'Key phrase extraction returns salient words or phrases from text. Detection, speech recognition, and regression solve visual, audio, and numeric tasks.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','medium','A system must identify each pixel that belongs to a road in a satellite image. Which vision task is required?','Semantic segmentation',['Image classification','Named entity recognition','Text generation'],'Semantic segmentation assigns a class to image pixels and can outline regions such as roads. Whole-image labels and language techniques do not provide pixel-level output.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','hard','A legal team needs a short faithful synopsis of each contract while retaining the original documents. Which workload fits?','Text summarization',['Image generation','Speech synthesis','Anomaly detection'],'Summarization condenses source text into a shorter account while the original remains the evidence. The other workloads create media or detect unusual numeric patterns.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','medium','A service must produce a natural-language answer that did not previously exist. Which workload category applies?','Generative AI',['Optical character recognition','Clustering','Anomaly detection'],'Generative AI creates new content such as a response. OCR extracts existing characters, while clustering and anomaly detection analyze patterns in data.'),
  dd('ai-workloads','easy','{{blank}} is the image task that predicts which known plant species appears in a photograph.','classification',['regression','translation','synthesis'],'Image classification assigns a known label to a whole image. Regression predicts a number, translation changes language, and synthesis creates audio.'),
  sg('ai-workloads','medium','Decide whether each capability matches the requested output.','true-false',[["OCR can return printed characters from an image",true],["Sentiment analysis returns bounding boxes around products",false],["Speech synthesis can create audio from text",true]],'OCR extracts visible text and speech synthesis creates spoken output. Bounding boxes are associated with object detection, not sentiment analysis.'),
  ms('ai-workloads','hard','Which TWO characteristics distinguish an agentic solution from a simple text generator?',['It can choose among configured tools','It can take sequenced actions toward a goal'],['It must always generate an image','It requires every step to be manually selected by the user'],'Agentic solutions can reason about available actions and use tools toward a goal. Image generation is optional, and fully manual step selection removes the defining autonomy.'),
  ms('ai-workloads','medium','Which TWO techniques analyze written customer comments without generating new text?',['Sentiment analysis','Named entity recognition'],['Speech synthesis','Image generation'],'Sentiment and entity recognition derive signals from existing text. Speech synthesis and image generation create new media outputs.'),

  mc('foundry-generative','easy','Where can a developer test prompts against a deployed model interactively in Microsoft Foundry?','A model playground',['Azure Cost Management','A virtual network peering blade','A storage lifecycle rule'],'A model playground provides an interactive inference experience for prompt testing. Cost, network, and storage management surfaces do not run model conversations.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','medium','An assistant must call an internal ticket API. What should be configured for the agent?','A function or API tool with scoped authentication',['An image-generation deployment','A public anonymous administrator key','A speech voice with a matching name'],'A controlled function or API tool exposes the intended operation to the agent with appropriate identity. Image and speech features do not call the ticket system, and anonymous admin access is unsafe.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','hard','A retrieved document contains text telling the agent to ignore its system instructions. How should the application treat that text?','As untrusted data that cannot replace higher-priority instructions',['As a new system prompt because it came from retrieval','As proof that every tool call is authorized','As a reason to disable input validation'],'Retrieved content can contain prompt injection and must remain untrusted context. It does not gain instruction priority or authorize actions, and validation should remain enabled.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','medium','A developer wants the agent to remember a customer’s preferred response language across sessions. Which capability is intended for this?','Agent memory',['File search over product manuals','Image classification','Batch transcription'],'Agent memory can retain relevant user-specific context across interactions. File search grounds knowledge, and vision or speech workloads do not provide conversational persistence.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','medium','What should a team use to inspect the sequence of model calls, retrieval, and tool execution?','Tracing',['Image captions','Storage redundancy','Speech pronunciation settings'],'Tracing records the execution path across model and tool steps and supports diagnosis. The other choices concern content or infrastructure rather than orchestration visibility.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','hard','A production app needs stable agent behavior while a new instruction set is tested. Which release practice should be used?','Publish and target a specific tested agent version',['Edit the live instructions without a version','Randomly alternate every request between drafts','Let clients choose an unpublished draft by default'],'Versioned publishing separates tested production behavior from ongoing changes. Direct edits, random drafts, or unpublished defaults make releases unpredictable.'),
  dd('foundry-generative','easy','A custom operation exposed to an agent is configured as a {{blank}}.','tool',['temperature','token','vision label'],'Tools give agents callable capabilities such as application functions. Temperature and tokens are model settings or units, while a vision label is an output.'),
  dd('foundry-generative','medium','The URL used by an SDK to access a specific Foundry project is the project {{blank}}.','endpoint',['tag','budget','availability set'],'The project endpoint tells the SDK where to access project resources and services. Tags, budgets, and availability sets are Azure management concepts rather than API locations.'),
  sg('foundry-generative','hard','Evaluate each statement about secure agent tools.','yes-no',[["Tool permissions should follow least privilege",true],["The model should receive every backend credential in its prompt",false],["The application should execute tool arguments without validation",false]],'Least privilege and input validation constrain what an agent can do. Prompting with backend credentials or executing unvalidated arguments creates unnecessary exposure and authority.'),
  ms('foundry-generative','medium','Which TWO prompt elements improve a request for consistent structured output?',['A clearly defined output schema','An example that follows the required structure'],['A request to be as creative as possible','An instruction to ignore missing required fields'],'Schemas and representative examples clarify the expected structure. Unbounded creativity and ignoring missing fields work against predictable, valid output.'),

  mc('foundry-text-speech','easy','Which capability can identify that a document is written in French?','Language detection',['Text translation','Object detection','Image generation'],'Language detection identifies the language without changing the content. Translation changes languages, while detection and generation in the other modalities do not inspect written language.'),
  mc('foundry-text-speech','medium','A transcript must indicate which participant spoke each segment. Which feature is needed?','Speaker diarization',['Sentiment polarity','Optical character recognition','Image segmentation'],'Speaker diarization separates and labels speakers within transcribed audio. Sentiment, OCR, and segmentation do not identify speakers.'),
  mc('foundry-text-speech','hard','A call recording is several hours long and can be processed after upload. Which transcription approach is appropriate?','Asynchronous batch transcription',['Text-to-speech synthesis','Real-time image analysis','Key phrase extraction without transcription'],'Batch transcription is suitable for stored long-form audio that does not require an immediate streaming result. The other options do not convert the recording to text.'),
  dd('foundry-text-speech','easy','Identifying product names in written reviews uses named {{blank}} recognition.','entity',['speaker','pixel','anomaly'],'Named entity recognition locates and categorizes mentions such as products in text. Speaker, pixel, and anomaly processing describe other tasks.'),
  sg('foundry-text-speech','medium','Evaluate each statement about speech processing.','true-false',[["Speech recognition converts audio into text",true],["Speech synthesis identifies sentiment in a transcript",false],["Speech translation can change spoken content into another language",true]],'Recognition transcribes audio and translation changes language. Speech synthesis produces audio from text and does not calculate sentiment.'),
  ms('foundry-text-speech','hard','Which TWO outputs can text analysis derive from support messages?',['Sentiment labels','Named entities'],['Bounding boxes around callers','Synthesized speech waveforms'],'Text analysis can return sentiment and entities from written messages. Bounding boxes are visual outputs and synthesized waveforms are generated audio.'),

  mc('foundry-vision','easy','A model must label a photograph as indoor or outdoor. Which capability is required?','Image classification',['Object detection','Speech recognition','Entity linking'],'Classification assigns a category to the whole image. Detection locates instances, while speech and entity linking work with other inputs.'),
  mc('foundry-vision','medium','A warehouse app must count pallets and return each pallet’s location in a photo. Which capability fits?','Object detection',['Image classification only','Sentiment analysis','Text summarization'],'Object detection can identify multiple instances and their bounding boxes, enabling a count and locations. A whole-image label cannot locate each pallet.'),
  mc('foundry-vision','medium','A model receives a chart image and a question asking which bar is largest. What capability does it need?','Multimodal visual reasoning',['Text-only completion','Batch transcription','Clustering without image input'],'The model must interpret the visual chart in the context of a written question. Text-only completion, audio transcription, and nonvisual clustering cannot inspect the bars.'),
  dd('foundry-vision','easy','Creating a new logo concept from a text description uses image {{blank}}.','generation',['recognition','classification','extraction'],'Image generation produces new visual content from a prompt. Recognition, classification, and extraction analyze existing content instead.'),
  sg('foundry-vision','hard','Evaluate each statement about visual workloads.','yes-no',[["OCR is appropriate for reading a serial number in a photo",true],["Image generation is the best way to locate existing defects",false],["A text-only deployment can always accept an image in its prompt",false]],'OCR reads visible characters, while locating defects requires analysis such as detection. Image inputs require a deployment with visual capability rather than any text-only model.'),

  mc('foundry-extraction','easy','An organization needs standard vendor, date, and total fields from invoices. What is the best starting point?','The prebuilt invoice analyzer',['A custom speech voice','An agent memory store','A model deployment with no extraction schema'],'A prebuilt invoice analyzer already targets common invoice fields and is the fastest grounded starting point. Speech, memory, and an undefined output do not meet the extraction requirement.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','medium','A custom analyzer confuses contract start and renewal dates. Which schema improvement is most useful?','Give each field a precise description and expected meaning',['Rename both fields to date','Increase generation randomness','Remove representative test documents'],'Clear distinct field definitions help the analyzer select the intended evidence. Ambiguous names, more randomness, and less testing make confusion more likely.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','hard','A video archive needs chapter summaries and time-aligned topics. Which Content Understanding input capability applies?','Video analysis',['Image generation','Text-only sentiment analysis','Speaker diarization alone'],'Content Understanding video analysis can produce time-grounded insights. Image generation and text-only sentiment do not process the source, while diarization alone only separates speakers.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','medium','An extracted field is absent from a source document. What should a well-designed result represent?','The field as missing rather than inventing a value',['A plausible value generated from unrelated documents','The most common value in the training set','A value copied from a different customer'],'Extraction should remain grounded in the supplied source and represent absent evidence as missing. Guessing or borrowing unrelated values creates unsupported data.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','hard','Why should extraction tests include scans with poor lighting and unusual layouts?','They reveal whether the analyzer works on representative variation',['They guarantee every future input will succeed','They increase the Azure subscription quota','They remove the need for confidence thresholds'],'Representative variation exposes real failure modes and informs thresholds or improvements. A test set cannot guarantee all future inputs or replace operational controls.'),
  sg('foundry-extraction','medium','Evaluate each statement about analyzer schemas.','true-false',[["A field description can clarify what evidence should be extracted",true],["A schema automatically adds facts that are absent from the input",false],["Field types help downstream applications consume structured output",true]],'Descriptions and types define a useful structured contract. The analyzer should not manufacture values when the input lacks supporting evidence.'),
  sg('foundry-extraction','easy','Decide whether each scenario is a Content Understanding use case.','yes-no',[["Extract line items and totals from purchase orders",true],["Create a new advertising illustration from a slogan",false],["Generate a fictional voice recording from a short script",false]],'Content Understanding extracts grounded structure and insights from supplied content. Creating a new illustration or voice recording is generation rather than extraction.'),
];

const p3 = [
  mc('responsible-ai','easy','An image-captioning service consistently produces lower-quality descriptions for assistive-technology users. Which principle should guide remediation?','Inclusiveness',['Clustering','Cost optimization','Speech translation'],'Inclusiveness considers whether the system works for people with different needs and abilities. The issue is user access and quality, not grouping, cost, or language conversion.'),
  mc('responsible-ai','medium','A team cannot explain who approved a model change that caused harmful outcomes. Which governance gap is most evident?','Accountability',['Object detection','Tokenization','Elasticity'],'Accountability requires defined owners, approval records, and responsibility for outcomes. Detection, tokenization, and elasticity do not address missing governance.'),
  dd('responsible-ai','easy','{{blank}} is evaluated by testing whether error rates differ across affected groups.','fairness',['model compression','image generation','throughput'],'Fairness evaluation looks for systematic differences in performance or outcomes across relevant groups. The alternatives describe model size, media generation, or capacity.'),
  sg('responsible-ai','hard','Evaluate each statement about privacy-aware AI design.','yes-no',[["Collect only data that is necessary for the stated purpose",true],["Store every prompt forever in case it becomes useful",false],["Make model interaction logs public to simplify troubleshooting",false]],'Data minimization and controlled access reduce privacy and security risk. Indefinite retention and public troubleshooting logs expand exposure without a defined need.'),
  ms('responsible-ai','medium','Which TWO actions support reliability and safety after deployment?',['Monitor failures and changes in production behavior','Define an escalation or fallback process'],['Assume test results never expire','Remove human intervention for every high-impact case'],'Monitoring detects changed behavior and escalation limits harm when the system is uncertain or failing. Permanent assumptions and eliminating oversight weaken safety.'),
  ms('responsible-ai','hard','Which TWO pieces of information improve transparency for users?',['The intended purpose and important limitations','Notice that AI is contributing to the interaction'],['Private credentials used by the backend','Proprietary model weights regardless of user need'],'Useful transparency explains AI involvement, purpose, and limitations without exposing secrets or irrelevant proprietary artifacts.'),

  mc('model-components','easy','A search system compares the semantic meaning of short passages. Which model output is most useful?','Embedding vectors',['Synthesized speech','Object bounding boxes','Azure cost forecasts'],'Embeddings represent semantic characteristics numerically and support similarity comparison. Audio, visual coordinates, and cost forecasts are unrelated outputs.'),
  mc('model-components','medium','A creative-writing assistant returns nearly identical drafts. Which setting could be raised cautiously to increase variation?','Temperature',['Maximum input length','RBAC role scope','Retrieval index count'],'Raising temperature can increase sampling variety, although outputs still require evaluation. Context length, permissions, and index count are not creativity controls.'),
  mc('model-components','hard','A smaller model meets quality and latency requirements in testing. Why might it be preferable to a larger model?','It can reduce cost and latency while preserving required quality',['It always has more current knowledge','It removes the need for monitoring','It guarantees no harmful output'],'A model that meets measured quality with lower operational cost or latency can be the better fit. Size does not guarantee freshness, safety, or freedom from monitoring.'),
  dd('model-components','medium','Supplying retrieved company documents with each request is called {{blank}} the model.','grounding',['clustering','segmenting','synthesizing'],'Grounding provides relevant external context for a response without changing model weights. Clustering, segmentation, and synthesis refer to other operations.'),
  sg('model-components','medium','Evaluate each statement about model context and output.','true-false',[["Input and output tokens contribute to model usage",true],["Maximum output tokens guarantees factual accuracy",false],["A deployment should be tested under expected concurrency",true]],'Token limits control capacity and usage but cannot guarantee correctness. Load testing is needed to understand latency and throughput under realistic concurrency.'),
  ms('model-components','hard','Which TWO factors should be compared before changing a production model deployment?',['Quality on representative evaluation cases','Latency and cost under expected use'],['The alphabetical order of model names','The color used for the deployment icon'],'A production selection should use measured task quality and operational performance. Display order and icon styling provide no evidence of model suitability.'),

  mc('ai-workloads','easy','A system predicts the expected wait time in minutes. Which task type is this?','Regression',['Binary classification','Clustering','OCR'],'A numeric duration is a continuous value suited to regression. Classification returns labels, clustering finds groups, and OCR reads visual text.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','medium','A model identifies whether an email expresses satisfaction, frustration, or neutrality. Which capability is being used?','Sentiment analysis',['Named entity recognition','Object detection','Language detection'],'Sentiment analysis estimates expressed opinion in text. Entity recognition finds names, object detection locates visual items, and language detection identifies the language used.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','easy','A camera system must read the characters on vehicle plates. Which capability is required?','Optical character recognition',['Image generation','Text summarization','Clustering'],'OCR extracts visible characters from images. Generation creates new images, summarization condenses language, and clustering groups data.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','medium','A model identifies mentions of dates, people, and companies in reports. Which text technique fits?','Named entity recognition',['Key phrase extraction only','Speech translation','Regression'],'Named entity recognition locates and categorizes specific mentions such as people, organizations, and dates. The other tasks do not produce those entity labels.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','hard','An autonomous support workflow chooses whether to search documentation, query an order system, or escalate. Which workload pattern is this?','Agentic AI',['Image classification','Batch transcription','Unsupervised clustering'],'An agentic workflow selects tools and actions toward a support goal. The alternatives analyze images, audio, or unlabeled data without action orchestration.'),
  mc('ai-workloads','medium','A service produces concise bullet points from a lengthy incident report. Which technique is required?','Summarization',['Entity linking','Object detection','Speech recognition'],'Summarization creates a shorter representation of source content. Entity linking, visual detection, and transcription produce different outputs.'),
  dd('ai-workloads','easy','{{blank}} discovers natural customer segments when no segment labels exist.','clustering',['classification','anomaly detection','image captioning'],'Clustering groups similar unlabeled observations. Classification needs target labels, anomaly detection finds unusual cases, and captioning describes visual content.'),
  sg('ai-workloads','medium','Decide whether each stated output matches the technique.','yes-no',[["Regression can predict a numeric energy demand",true],["Image classification returns a bounding box for every object",false],["Key phrase extraction returns a complete spoken narration",false]],'Regression returns numbers. Per-object locations come from object detection rather than image classification, and speech synthesis—not key phrase extraction—creates narration.'),
  ms('ai-workloads','hard','Which TWO inputs can a multimodal model use together for visual question answering?',['An image','A text question about the image'],['An Azure subscription invoice only as billing metadata','A speech voice name with no audio or image content'],'Visual question answering combines image content with language instructions. Billing metadata and a voice name do not provide the visual evidence or question.'),
  ms('ai-workloads','medium','Which TWO scenarios are information-extraction workloads?',['Return named fields from a scanned form','Return structured events and timestamps from a video'],['Create a fictional landscape image','Read a response aloud'],'Extraction derives grounded structure from supplied content. Creating an image and synthesizing speech generate new media instead.'),

  mc('foundry-generative','easy','A developer needs a quick no-code way to configure agent instructions and tools in Foundry. Which agent type should be selected?','Prompt agent',['Hosted agent with a custom container','Content Understanding analyzer','Azure virtual machine scale set'],'Prompt agents are configured through instructions, models, and tools without a custom orchestration runtime. Hosted agents and the other resources serve different needs.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','medium','A team already runs custom agent code and wants to call Foundry models through a common API. Which API family is designed for model responses and tools?','The Responses API',['The Azure DNS API','The Cost Management exports API','The Storage lifecycle API'],'The Responses API provides a model interaction surface that can support tools and response state. DNS, cost, and storage APIs do not perform generative inference.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','hard','An agent can delete customer records. Which authorization design is safest?','Expose a narrowly scoped operation and require verified user permission',['Give the agent a subscription Owner credential','Use one shared administrator key for all users','Authorize deletion whenever the model sounds confident'],'A high-impact tool should expose only the required action and enforce application identity and user authorization. Broad or shared credentials and model confidence are not authorization.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','medium','A product assistant must cite uploaded manuals and decline unsupported questions. Which configuration best fits?','File search plus instructions to answer only from retrieved evidence',['Higher temperature without retrieval','Code interpreter without the manuals','Image generation with a product logo'],'File search supplies relevant manual passages, while explicit instructions define behavior when evidence is missing. Sampling or unrelated tools cannot provide grounded product facts.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','medium','A team needs to compare prompt variants over a fixed evaluation set. What should it record?','Task-quality metrics and the tested prompt or deployment version',['Only the visually preferred response','The browser zoom used by the tester','A random answer with no input record'],'Repeatable evaluation records the version, inputs, and relevant quality measures. Appearance or untracked random examples cannot support a controlled comparison.'),
  mc('foundry-generative','hard','Why should an application validate structured model output before using it in a database update?','Model output can be malformed or contain unsupported values',['Validation increases the model context window','Validation automatically grants database permissions','Validation makes retrieval unnecessary'],'Generated output is untrusted application input and must satisfy the expected schema and business rules. Validation does not alter context, authorization, or knowledge grounding.'),
  dd('foundry-generative','easy','A deployed agent uses file {{blank}} to retrieve uploaded documents.','search',['synthesis','classification','translation'],'File search retrieves relevant content from files for grounded responses. The other terms describe media or classification operations.'),
  dd('foundry-generative','medium','Use {{blank}} records to inspect model and tool execution steps.','traces',['embeddings','invoices','subnets'],'Traces capture the path through model, retrieval, and tool operations for diagnosis. Embeddings represent content, invoices are documents, and subnets are network boundaries.'),
  sg('foundry-generative','hard','Evaluate each statement about prompt design.','true-false',[["A system prompt can define enduring behavior and boundaries",true],["A user prompt should automatically override every safety instruction",false],["Examples can clarify the required response format",true]],'System instructions establish higher-priority behavior, and examples can make output expectations concrete. User input does not automatically supersede system or safety controls.'),
  ms('foundry-generative','medium','Which TWO practices support a secure lightweight Foundry client?',['Use a managed identity or other supported credential','Keep privileged credentials out of public client code'],['Place an administrator key in the system prompt','Allow anonymous access to every project tool'],'Supported identity and server-side secret handling reduce credential exposure. Prompt-embedded administrator keys and anonymous tools create excessive risk.'),

  mc('foundry-text-speech','easy','Which text capability can find order numbers and product names in a message?','Named entity recognition',['Sentiment analysis','Image segmentation','Regression'],'Named entity recognition finds and categorizes specified mentions in text. Sentiment estimates opinion, segmentation labels image pixels, and regression predicts numbers.'),
  mc('foundry-text-speech','medium','A service must translate live spoken Spanish into English text. Which capability should it use?','Speech translation',['Text-to-speech only','Image classification','Key phrase extraction only'],'Speech translation recognizes spoken input and translates it to a target language. Synthesis and the other analytical tasks do not perform that end-to-end conversion.'),
  mc('foundry-text-speech','hard','A transcription system often misses product codes. What is an appropriate first adaptation?','Supply a phrase list containing expected product codes',['Increase image resolution','Use a resource lock','Generate a new logo'],'A phrase list supplies contextual vocabulary that can improve recognition of expected terms. Visual, governance, and image-generation changes do not affect transcription.'),
  dd('foundry-text-speech','easy','Separating speakers in a meeting transcript is called speaker {{blank}}.','diarization',['segmentation','generation','classification'],'Speaker diarization identifies which speaker produced each segment of audio. The other terms do not specifically assign transcript segments to speakers.'),
  sg('foundry-text-speech','medium','Evaluate each statement about text analysis.','yes-no',[["Summarization can condense a long conversation",true],["Key phrase extraction creates a complete audio narration",false],["Sentiment analysis returns the location of every object in a photo",false]],'Summarization condenses language. Key phrase extraction returns text fragments rather than audio, and sentiment analysis estimates opinion rather than locating visual objects.'),
  ms('foundry-text-speech','hard','Which TWO components are needed for a conventional voice assistant pipeline?',['Speech recognition before language processing','Speech synthesis after a text response is produced'],['Image segmentation before transcription','Object detection after every answer'],'A conventional voice pipeline transcribes spoken input and synthesizes the resulting text response. Visual segmentation and detection are unrelated.'),

  mc('foundry-vision','easy','A moderation workflow needs to label an uploaded image with one of several known content categories. Which task fits?','Image classification',['Visual question answering','Optical character recognition','Regression'],'Image classification selects a known category for the overall image. Visual question answering responds about image content, OCR reads visible text, and regression predicts numbers.'),
  mc('foundry-vision','medium','A maintenance app needs the coordinates of each corroded area in a photograph. Which output should the model produce?','Detected regions or bounding boxes',['A single sentiment label','A spoken transcript','A cluster of customer records'],'Locations of multiple visual defects require detection regions or boxes. Sentiment, transcripts, and customer clustering do not represent image locations.'),
  mc('foundry-vision','medium','A model is asked to compare two diagrams supplied with a text instruction. Which capability is essential?','A deployment that accepts visual inputs',['A text-only embedding index','Text sentiment analysis','Batch audio transcription'],'The task requires a deployment capable of interpreting images with text. Text-only embeddings, sentiment analysis, and audio transcription cannot inspect diagrams.'),
  dd('foundry-vision','easy','Finding the location of a bicycle in an image uses object {{blank}}.','detection',['synthesis','translation','summarization'],'Object detection identifies and locates visual instances. Synthesis, translation, and summarization do not return object positions.'),
  sg('foundry-vision','hard','Evaluate each statement about image generation and analysis.','true-false',[["Image generation creates new visual output from instructions",true],["OCR is intended to create a new photograph",false],["Visual analysis can describe content in an existing image",true]],'Generation creates new imagery, while OCR reads text from existing imagery and visual analysis interprets existing content. These are different workload directions.'),

  mc('foundry-extraction','easy','A claims system needs policy number and incident date from standard forms. What should it use first?','A suitable prebuilt or custom document analyzer',['Key phrase extraction only','An image generator','A clustering model with no schema'],'A document analyzer extracts defined fields from supplied forms. Key phrases, image creation, and unsupervised grouping do not produce the required grounded structure.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','medium','A custom field should contain one value from a controlled list of product categories. Which schema field behavior is appropriate?','Classification against the allowed categories',['Free-form image generation','Speaker diarization','Numeric regression without categories'],'A classification field constrains the result to an allowed category set. Image, speaker, and unconstrained numeric tasks do not meet that structured contract.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','hard','A recorded interview needs transcript, participants, and time-grounded topics. Which analyzer modality fits?','Audio analysis',['Image-only analysis','Text-to-speech generation','Tabular regression'],'An audio analyzer can derive transcript and time-related insights from the recording. Image, speech output, and tabular prediction do not analyze the supplied audio.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','medium','An extraction result includes a value and its page region. What is the page region useful for?','Showing the source evidence that supports the value',['Increasing the maximum output tokens','Assigning an Azure role','Choosing a speech voice'],'A grounded source region lets a user or workflow verify where the extracted value came from. It does not configure generation, authorization, or speech.'),
  mc('foundry-extraction','hard','An analyzer works on sample PDFs but fails on mobile photographs. What should the next evaluation add?','Representative photographed documents with realistic quality variation',['Only more copies of the original PDFs','Higher model temperature without new tests','A public administrator credential'],'Evaluation should include the actual input modality and quality variation expected in production. Duplicate clean PDFs, randomness, or unsafe credentials do not diagnose the gap.'),
  dd('foundry-extraction','easy','A reusable definition of fields and processing behavior in Content Understanding is an {{blank}}.','analyzer',['availability zone','action group','embedding vector'],'An analyzer defines how Content Understanding processes content and which structured outputs it returns. Infrastructure zones, alert targets, and embeddings are different concepts.'),
  sg('foundry-extraction','medium','Evaluate each statement about extraction confidence and review.','yes-no',[["A low-confidence consequential field can be routed to a person",true],["A confidence score proves that a value is correct",false],["Business thresholds should reflect the cost of extraction errors",true]],'Confidence is a workflow signal, not a guarantee. Validation thresholds and human review should reflect the consequences of incorrect extracted values.'),
];

